Nomura Securities Co Ltd is seeking apossible business relationship with Kidder Peabody and Co Inc,said Setsuya Tabuchi, the chairman of the board of Nomura.    Tabuchi told an investment conference "at present thecompany's staff (of Nomura) has been studying the possiblity ofa joint buiness," he said.    Tabuchi said he has not been informed how far the study hasprogressed. He declined to elaborate further.    Kidder Peabody is a wholly-owned subsidiary of GeneralElectric &lt;GE>. Kidder officials were not immediately availablefor comment. Reuter&#3;